Bots are third-party applications that run inside Telegram. Users can interact
with bots by sending them messages, commands and inline requests. You control
your bots using HTTPS requests to Telegram's Bot API.

Bot API - The Bot API is an HTTP-based interface created for developers keen
on building bots for Telegram.

Capabilities:
1. Customized notifications and news
2. Provide content from other platforms
3. Custom tools (weather, translations etc)
4. Anything


How bots work:
https://core.telegram.org/bots#6-botfather

Messages, commands and requests sent by users are passed to the software
running on your servers. Our intermediary server handles all encryption and
communication with the Telegram API for you. You communicate with this server
via a simple HTTPS-interface that offers a simplified version of the Telegram API.

